    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Seat Tracks</title>
        <para>Seat track requirements (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f4700690">Fig. 90, Item 3</hotlnk>) are available for various seat configurations and seat
            type applications. Seat track and wheel chair tie downs are available for different configuration of seating
            plans when required. The tracks are mounted to the floor and use a stud and locking clip (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f4700690">Fig. 90, Items 1 and 2</hotlnk>) to allow the movement of seat rows as required.
        </para>
        <figure id="f4700690" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/g4700690.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <caption>Figure 90. Seat Track and Seat Mounting Studs</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. SEAT MOUNTING STUD</callout1>
                <callout1>2. SEAT STUD RETAINER CLIP</callout1>
                <callout1>3. SEAT TRACK</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>Seat track may be installed to facilitate various width seat rows.</para>
        <figure id="f4700691" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/g4700691.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <caption>Figure 91. Seat Track and Seat Mounting Base</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. SEAT ASSEMBLY LEGS</callout1>
                <callout1>2. SEAT MOUNTING STUDS AND NUTS</callout1>
                <callout1>3. SEAT TRACK</callout1>
                <callout1>4. RIBBED ISLE FLOORING</callout1>
                <callout1>5. SEAT MOUNTING BASE</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <para>
            <title>Wheel Chair Shoulder Harness Mounting and Storage</title>
        </para>
        <para>Shoulder harness tracks (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f4700692">Fig. 92, Item 2</hotlnk>) are an available option used in conjunction with wheel
            chair wheel floor track. The seat belt and harness assembly are stored in a secured carrying bag (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f4700693">Fig. 93, Item 2</hotlnk>) attached to the shoulder harness track assembly.
        </para>
        <figure id="f4700692" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/g4700692.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="288px"
                     scalefitheight="288px"/>
            <caption>Figure 92. Shoulder Harness Track</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. SHOULDER HARNESS ATTACHMENT ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>2. SHOULDER HARNESS TRACK</callout1>
                <callout1>3. SHOULDER HARNESS TRACK TORQUE HEAD MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                <callout1>4. SHOULDER HARNESS BELT</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f4700693" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/g4700693.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
            <caption>Figure 93. Shoulder Harness Storage Bag</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. HARNESS BAG MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                <callout1>2. SHOULDER HARNESS STORAGE BAG</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
